<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Charles Follo was assistant director of University of Michigan Extension Service for programs in the Upper Peninsula. In addition he served as delegate to the Michigan Constitutional Convention of 1961-1962 and chairman of the Human Resources Council of the Upper Peninsula Committee for Area Programs.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The collection consists of three series: Constitutional Convention Delegate File; Upper Peninsula Committee for Area Progress (UPCAP) Human Resources Council papers; and University of Michigan Extension Service. The bulk of the collection relates to the constitutional convention and includes a diary of his convention experiences, correspondence with constituents and interest groups, and subject files on the issues discussed at the convention.  Some of his correspondents included Alvin M. Bentley, Prentiss M. Brown, and Neil Staebler.</p>
</scopecontent>

